# Kabang Docker Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and configure as needed

# ============================================
# Database Configuration
# ============================================

# SQLite (Default)
# No configuration needed - SQLite is used by default when POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING is empty
# Database file will be created at ./data/sqlite.db

# PostgreSQL (Optional)
# Set POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING to use PostgreSQL instead of SQLite
# Uncomment and set your connection string:

# POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING=postgresql://user:password@host:5432/database?sslmode=require

# Examples:
# - Neon: POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING=postgresql://user:pass@host.neon.tech/db?sslmode=require
# - Supabase: POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING=postgresql://postgres.[project]:[password]@aws-0-[region].pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres
# - Self-hosted: POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/dbname

# ============================================
# Quick Start Guide
# ============================================
# 
# SQLite (Default - Easiest):
#   1. docker-compose up -d
#   2. Access app at http://localhost:5674
#   3. Data persists in ./data/sqlite.db
#
# PostgreSQL (For production/scaling):
#   1. Set POSTGRES_CONNECTION_STRING above with your PostgreSQL connection string
#   2. docker-compose up -d
#   3. Access app at http://localhost:5674
#
# ============================================
